headline: Phillips 66 (PSX): Margin Decline Challenges Bull Case Heading Into Earnings Season
summary: Phillips 66 (PSX) is projected to grow earnings by an impressive 25.9% annually, far exceeding the US market’s 15.7% pace. Over the last five years, the company has become profitable, posting average annual earnings growth of 22.2%, but its net profit margin narrowed to 1.1% from last year’s 2.3%. Looking ahead, investors face a mixed backdrop as revenue is expected to contract by 2.3% per year while the share price trades at $137.07, well below a discounted cash flow fair value estimate of...
